    "Second, it also complicates accountability, as the collective nature of authorship dilutes personal responsibility, making it difficult to identify who is responsible for specific errors or misconduct.",
    "Consequently, these issues can affect both the willingness of scientists to engage in collaborative research and the integrity of the findings produced.",
    "Moreover, these new forms of collaborative authorship presented new challenges also in the context of power relations, namely in the hierarchical context of academia (see Macfarlane 2015).",
